href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgu1665702774669.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgu1665702774669.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgu1665702774669.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526441\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526441\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 15, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cgu1665702774669.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cgu1665702774669.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cgu1665702774669.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cgu1665702774669\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Installation and Configuration of PGS Connector\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The PGS connector makes use of ODBC to connect to PostgreSQL database. You must therefore install the PostgreSQL ODBC driver before connecting Uniface to your PostgreSQL database.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__section_w373ab1b5b3_w374ab1b5_w375ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1121024e51\">\n                       \n Installation\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57260e1_d57261e1_d57262e1\">It is assumed that you have already installed a supported version of the PostgreSQL DBMS server.</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26093e1_d26094e1_d26095e1\">Obtain and install a supported version of the\n               PostgreSQL client ODBC driver from <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://www.postgresql.org/\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.postgresql.org/</a>. For supported versions, see\n               the Uniface <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://community.rocketsoftware.com/rocket-uniface-product-updates-108/uniface-product-availability-information-18191\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Availability Matrix</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26096e1_d26097e1_d26098e1\">Set up the DSN (Data Source Name) and database in\n               ODBC. Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Control Panel &gt;ODBC</span></span> and follow the instructions on screen. <p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57266e1_d57267e1_d57268e1\">For example, define a <code class=\"ph codeph\">System\n                     DSN</code>, and select <code class=\"ph codeph\">PostgreSQL Unicode</code>. </p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__note_w382ab1b5b3b5b3b5_w383ab1b5b3b5b3_w384ab1b5b3b5_w385ab1b5b3_w386ab1b5_w387ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> It is strongly recommended that you use the Unicode PostgreSQL.</div>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__fig_d57269e1_d57270e1_d57271e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>PostgreSQL ODBC Driver Configuration</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"PostgreSQL ODBC Driver Configuration\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/pgsodbd_dsn.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__note_w388ab1b5b3b5b3b9_w389ab1b5b3b5b3_w390ab1b5b3b5_w391ab1b5b3_w392ab1b5_w393ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The PGS connector ignores the user and password defined in the ODBC\n                  Driver Setup.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26099e1_d26100e1_d26101e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Datasource</span> to edit\n               Advanced options. <p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57275e1_d57276e1_d57277e1\">Disable the\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">LF&lt;-&gt; CR/LF conversion</span> and set <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Level of\n                     rollback on errors</span> to <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Statement</span>. </p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__note_w394ab1b5b3b5b5b5_w395ab1b5b3b5b5_w396ab1b5b3b5_w397ab1b5b3_w398ab1b5_w399ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> These settings prevent problems with overflow tables and segmented\n                  fields.</div>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__fig_d57278e1_d57279e1_d57280e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Advanced Options</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Advanced Options\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/pgsodbc_dsn_options.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__section_w376ab1b5b5_w377ab1b5_w378ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1121024e141\">\n                       \n Configuring Database Access\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57287e1_d57288e1_d57289e1\">To configure Uniface to access a PostgreSQL database, edit the application assignment file. For example, you can edit the Uniface assignment file <span class=\"ph filepath\">dbms.asn</span> located in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/adm</span> directory of the Uniface installation.</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26102e1_d26103e1_d26104e1\">In the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section, declare the PGS\n               connector and set any required connector options. For example: <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nPGS U1.4\nUSYS$PGS_PARAMS identifiers = quoted</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57290e1_d57291e1_d57292e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lrr1665702733764.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lrr1665702733764.html\" title=\"You can assign connector options by setting USYS$PGS_PARAMS in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file.\">PGS Connector Options</a>. </p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26105e1_d26106e1_d26107e1\">In the [PATHS] section, define a logical path to\n               the PostgreSQL database you want to access. <p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57293e1_d57294e1_d57295e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$DBMS_DEF</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">PGS:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Data Source</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Schema</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">User</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>\n</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26108e1_d26109e1_d26110e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$DBMS_DEF</code>—the default\n                     logical path Uniface uses for the application database. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26111e1_d26112e1_d26113e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">DataSource</var>—connection\n                     string for the ODBC Data Source Name (DSN). For example:\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">PostgreSQL35W</code>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26114e1_d26115e1_d26116e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Schema</var>—name of a schema\n                     in the <var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>. For example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">public</code>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26117e1_d26118e1_d26119e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">UserName</var> and\n                        <var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>—user and password for the database. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57296e1_d57297e1_d57298e1\">For example:</p><p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">[PATHS] $DBMS_DEF\n                        PGS:PostgreSQL35W:public|signor|<var class=\"keyword varname\">password</var></code></p><p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57299e1_d57300e1_d57301e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qpp1665702522210.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qpp1665702522210.html\" title=\"You can configure Uniface to access any supported database for the Repository or application data.\">Configuring the Database Connector</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lnl1665702774754.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnl1665702774754.html\" title=\"Uniface automatically opens the DBMS when a read or write ProcScript statement is issued. The path and logon details for the specific database (or databases) can be provided in an assignment file, a command line instruction, or in the open ProcScript instruction.\">Database Access</a>, and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nci1665702524490.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nci1665702524490.html\" title=\"A path-to-connector assignment describes how to access a specific resource via the appropriate network or database connector. It defines the path name, and assigns it to a configuration that specifies the connector to use, the name and location of the resource, and the credentials required to log on to it. Paths are defined in the [PATHS] section of the application assignment file.\">Path-to-Connector Assignments</a>. </p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__section_w379ab1b5b7_w380ab1b5_w381ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1121024e286\">\n                       \n Using PostgreSQL as the Uniface Repository\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__p_d57305e1_d57306e1_d57307e1\">PostgreSQL can be used for the Uniface Repository. To do so:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26120e1_d26121e1_d26122e1\">Use the SQL scripts provided with the installation kit to create the Repository. Edit the scripts before running them to add a <code class=\"ph codeph\">set schema</code> statement (<code class=\"ph codeph\">set schema 'public';</code>). These scripts create the necessary tables, indexes, triggers, and stored procedures.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgu1665702774669__li_d26123e1_d26124e1_d26125e1\">In the <span class=\"ph filepath\">dbms.asn</span> file located in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/adm</span> directory, define a path to point to the PGS logon path. For example:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$PGS PGS:</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jbc1665702541838.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Repository</a><p>The Uniface Repository is a Unicode-enabled relational database used to store the definitions of Uniface Development Objects.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526441\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526441\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Installation and Configuration of PGS Connector Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 15, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Installation and Configuration of PGS Connector The PGS connector makes use of ODBC to connect to PostgreSQL database. You must therefore install the PostgreSQL ODBC driver before connecting Uniface to your PostgreSQL database. Installation It is assumed that you have already installed a supported version of the PostgreSQL DBMS server. Obtain and install a supported version of the PostgreSQL client ODBC driver from https://www.postgresql.org/ . For supported versions, see the Uniface Platform Availability Matrix . Set up the DSN (Data Source Name) and database in ODBC. Choose Control Panel >ODBC and follow the instructions on screen. For example, define a System DSN , and select PostgreSQL Unicode . Note: It is strongly recommended that you use the Unicode PostgreSQL. Figure 1. PostgreSQL ODBC Driver Configuration Note: The PGS connector ignores the user and password defined in the ODBC Driver Setup. Click Datasource to edit Advanced options. Disable the LF<-> CR/LF conversion and set Level of rollback on errors to Statement . Note: These settings prevent problems with overflow tables and segmented fields. Figure 2. Advanced Options Configuring Database Access To configure Uniface to access a PostgreSQL database, edit the application assignment file. For example, you can edit the Uniface assignment file dbms.asn located in the /common/adm directory of the Uniface installation. In the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section, declare the PGS connector and set any required connector options. For example: [DRIVER_SETTINGS] PGS U1.4 USYS$PGS_PARAMS identifiers = quoted Copy For more information, see PGS Connector Options . In the [PATHS] section, define a logical path to the PostgreSQL database you want to access. $DBMS_DEF PGS: Data Source : Schema | User | Password $DBMS_DEF —the default logical path Uniface uses for the application database. DataSource —connection string for the ODBC Data Source Name (DSN). For example: PostgreSQL35W . Schema —name of a schema in the Database . For example: public . UserName and Password —user and password for the database. For example: [PATHS] $DBMS_DEF PGS:PostgreSQL35W:public|signor| password For more information, see Configuring the Database Connector , Database Access , and Path-to-Connector Assignments . Using PostgreSQL as the Uniface Repository PostgreSQL can be used for the Uniface Repository. To do so: Use the SQL scripts provided with the installation kit to create the Repository. Edit the scripts before running them to add a set schema statement ( set schema 'public'; ). These scripts create the necessary tables, indexes, triggers, and stored procedures. In the dbms.asn file located in the /common/adm directory, define a path to point to the PGS logon path. For example: [PATHS] $PGS PGS: Copy Related Links Uniface Repository The Uniface Repository is a Unicode-enabled relational database used to store the definitions of Uniface Development Objects. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}